<div class="box">
<div class="doc"><p>Having had enough of talking about serious modules for a while, here's
a silly module that tickled my fancy. It's an implementation of the
Solitaire cypher system used in <li><a href="http://www.amazon.co.uk/exec/obidos/ASIN/0099410672">Cryptonomicon</a></li> that means you can
encrypt and decrypt things relatively securely just with a shuffled
deck of cards.</p>
<p>Of course, playing for hours with cards isn't much fun when all you're
trying to do is decrypt a message...which is where this module comes
in. The interface provided is much better than the golf one presented
in the book ;-)</p>
</div>
<div class="mylink"><a href="http://search.cpan.org/perldoc?Crypt::Solitaire">[Read the documentation for Crypt::Solitaire on search.cpan.org]</a></div>
</div>



